{
  "text": "SSQ -sum of squares; df -degree of freedom; MSQ -mean square; A, B, and C -linear terms; A \u00d7 B, A \u00d7 C, and B \u00d7 C -interactive terms; A 2 , B 2 , and C 2 -quadratic terms of J. marinum observed in fed-batch fermenter cultures (4.48 g/l per day) were somewhat higher than those obtained by S. limacinum SR21 (3.06 g/l per day in batch regime) grown on crude glycerol [CITATION_1] ). The P X was also higher than that ob-tained for S. limacinum (3.71 g/l per day) and J. marinum (3.27 g/l per day) in previous work with pure glycerol in WSM medium [CITATION_2] ). This can be ascribed to differences in the compositions of SWW between the two studies. Czech Journal of Food Sciences, 37, 2019 (5): 383-390 https://doi.org/10.17221/172/2018-CJFS",
